# README Structure Rule

## Purpose & Scope

This rule defines the standard structure for README.md files to ensure consistency and completeness across projects.

**Applies to**: Root `README.md` and module-level `README.md`.

## Inputs (Contract)

- Project/Module Name
- Description
- Setup/Usage instructions

## Outputs (Contract)

- Well-structured `README.md`

## Deterministic Steps

1. Create/Update `README.md`.
2. Ensure required sections exist:
   - Title
   - Description
   - Installation/Setup
   - Usage
   - Contribution
3. Use clear markdown formatting.

## Formatting Requirements

- Top-level H1 for Title
- H2 for main sections
- Badges (optional) at top

## OPSEC and Leak Control

- No internal secrets in README.

## Integration Points

None.

## Failure Modes and Recovery

N/A

## Provenance Footer Specification

N/A

## Related Rules

- `rule.authoring.file-structure.v1`

## FINAL MUST-PASS CHECKLIST

- [ ] Title and Description present
- [ ] Installation/Usage instructions present
- [ ] Consistent markdown structure
